The move by Nick comes at a time when networks face a backlash over the potentially negative impacts of TV viewing. This weekend they are getting some help from an unlikely source : Nickelodeon, the No. 1 network for children, is replacing its usual Saturday afternoon lineup with a message encouraging young viewers to go outside and play. High-profile reports have linked television watching to childhood obesity, for example. Marva Smalls, executive vice president for public affairs at Nickelodeon, acknowledged that awareness about childhood obesity is up, but said the network's initiatives were not a response to outside pressure. 